The paper discusses the constituent properties of resilience in software and organizational systems, which falls under the domain of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also analyzes case studies of software systems, which may fall under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The discussion of the ability to perceive environmental changes and plan adjustments may relate to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The analysis of resilience methods in computer systems may fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new way of reasoning about resilience, which may relate to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
